history.content: As you may know, since you are undeclared, you should not waitlist Upper Division CS courses, because you will be purged from the waitlist (this fall, major apps are likely to be processed after waitlist processing). You should look into Upper Division Tech Electives. You can find a list of these courses here: http://guide.berkeley.edu/undergraduate/degree-programs/computer-science/#majorrequirementstext.

There are a lot of courses on the list that won't restrict enrollment based on major.
See @2309. As student above have noted in phase 1, sign up for tech electives or EE 16A.

children.subject: No, you will have to waitlist. EE 16A seats are only reserved for undeclared if you are first-year.

history.content: Hello, I’m having a hard time planning what to Phase I for next semester. To provide some background about me, I am in L&S and undeclared. After this semester (Fall 2016), I will have completed all the CS lower division courses and I’ve already completed all my math and L&S breadth requirements as well. This means that I will submit my major application before the end of this semester. I have not yet taken EE16A or any of the upper division CS classes. What am I supposed to Phase I? Thank you!
